extracted_text:
Residential system. Solar collectors shall be considered an accessory use and
conform to the lesser of 6,000 sq.ft. or 10% of the lot size and are subject to setback
standards in Section 21-285.
llm_outputs.rationale: The extracted text specifies the maximum lot coverage for solar collectors as an accessory use in residential systems, which is the lesser of 6,000 sq.ft. or 10% of the lot size. This falls within our definition of max_lot_coverage for single-family homes in the RR district.
